, {"version": "diamond", "text": "Any frontal attack is repulsed. It is a docile Pok\u00e9mon that feeds on grass and berries."}, {"version": "heartgold", "text": "When attacked, they form a wall. Their rock-hard faces serve to protect them from the attacks."}, {"version": "legends-arceus", "text": "Its face is sturdy\u2014as strong as diamond\u2014and this hardness offers a very stable defense. Much about this species is still unknown, such as its natural habitat."}, {"version": "moon", "text": "It lived in the same environments as Rampardos. Their fossils have been found together\u2014 seemingly from after they\u2019d fought to the finish."}, {"version": "omega-ruby", "text": "When they lined up side by side, no foe could break through. They shielded their young in that way."}, {"version": "pearl", "text": "When attacked, they form a wall with their shieldlike faces to protect their young."}, {"version": "platinum", "text": "When they lined up side by side, no foe could break through. They shielded their young in that way."}, {"version": "soulsilver", "text": "When attacked, they form a wall. Their rock-hard faces serve to protect them from the attacks."}, {"version": "sun", "text": "While it can guard against any sort of attack from the front, it is left without recourse when attacked from behind."}, {"version": "ultra-moon", "text": "This Pok\u00e9mon is from roughly 100 million years ago. Its terrifyingly tough face is harder than steel."}, {"version": "ultra-sun", "text": "The bones of its face are huge and hard, so they were mistaken for its spine until after this Pok\u00e9mon was successfully restored."}, {"version": "white", "text": "When they lined up side by side, no foe could break through. They shielded their young in that way."}, {"version": "white-2", "text": "When they lined up side by side, no foe could break through. They shielded their young in that way."}, {"version": "x", "text": "When they lined up side by side, no foe could break through. They